# Development Guidelines

## TypeScript Usage
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Ensure proper type definitions in `src/types`
- Avoid using `any` type - prefer explicit typing

## Component Guidelines
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Place reusable components in `src/components`
- Follow the component naming convention: PascalCase
- Implement proper prop typing for all components

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Custom CSS should be minimal and placed in `src/app/globals.css`
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles
- Use Tailwind's configuration for extending theme

## Code Quality
- Follow ESLint rules defined in [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs)
- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Keep components small and focused

## Performance
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Implement proper loading states
- Optimize API calls and data fetching
- Follow React best practices for performance




